  {
    "title": "Boab Prison Tree",
    "rating": 5,
    "travelDate": "2022-10",
    "publishedDate": "2022-10-16",
    "text": "The Historic Baobab tree is situated in front of Kasane  Police Station.  which was hollowed out and used to hold up to 14 people.This particular Baobab tree played a major role in the administration of justice, distribution of mail and labour recruitments in northern Botswana. It was used as a gaol before the advent of modern prisons in the area.\nThe prison baobab has some cavities which served as prison cells in historic times. There are some windows like openings which appear to have provided both light and ventilation into these prison cell.",
    "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.com/ShowUserReviews-g297318-d13951354-r864820997-Boab_Prison_Tree-Kasane_Chobe_National_Park_North_West_District.html",
